# AI Integration (Gemini + ElevenLabs)

## Overview

All AI text generation lives in `src/utils/geminiAI.ts`. TTS (text-to-speech) lives in `src/utils/tts.ts`. Training AI in `src/utils/pokerTraining.ts`.

Per-group API keys stored in `settings` table (`gemini_api_key`, `elevenlabs_api_key`), mapped via `toSettings`/`settingsToRow` in `supabaseCache.ts`. All calls routed through Vercel Edge Functions via `src/utils/apiProxy.ts`. Key priority: (1) group settings key sent in request body, (2) Vercel env var fallback (`GEMINI_API_KEY`, `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`), (3) error. Owner manages keys in Settings > AI tab. `getGeminiApiKey()` and `getElevenLabsApiKey()` return the group key or `'server-managed'`.

## API Proxy Architecture

All external API calls are centralized through `src/utils/apiProxy.ts`:
- `proxyGeminiGenerate(version, model, apiKey, payload)` → `/api/gemini` or direct Google URL
- `proxyGeminiGenerateWithSignal(...)` → same with AbortSignal support (for TTS timeouts)
- `proxyGeminiModels(apiKey, version)` → `/api/gemini-models` or direct Google URL
- `proxyElevenLabsTTS(apiKey, voiceId, payload, format, signal)` → `/api/elevenlabs-tts` or direct ElevenLabs
- `proxyElevenLabsUsage(apiKey)` → `/api/elevenlabs-usage` or direct ElevenLabs

**NEVER add direct `generativelanguage.googleapis.com` or `api.elevenlabs.io` URLs in `src/` files.** Always use the proxy functions.

## Vercel Edge Functions (`api/` directory)

| Route | Method | Key Source | Proxies To |
|-------|--------|-----------|-----------|
| `/api/gemini` | POST | Body `apiKey` → env `GEMINI_API_KEY` | `generativelanguage.googleapis.com/.../generateContent` |
| `/api/gemini-models` | POST | Body `apiKey` → env `GEMINI_API_KEY` | `generativelanguage.googleapis.com/.../models` |
| `/api/elevenlabs-tts` | POST | Body `apiKey` → env `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` | `api.elevenlabs.io/v1/text-to-speech` |
| `/api/elevenlabs-usage` | POST | Body `apiKey` → env `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY` | `api.elevenlabs.io/v1/user/subscription` |

All Edge Functions verify Supabase JWT (`api/_auth.ts`) and accept per-group API keys in the request. Non-admin users see cached AI content via Supabase Realtime sync.

### Thinking Model Token Limits
Gemini 3 Flash (thinking model) uses tokens from `maxOutputTokens` for internal reasoning. Allocate generous limits:
- `generateGraphInsights`: 4096 tokens
- `generateForecastComparison`: 1024 tokens
- Standard generation: keep defaults reasonable (~1024-2048)

